# No Unicode in Code

## Rule
**NEVER use Unicode characters (including emojis, special symbols, checkmarks, etc.) in any code files.**

## Scope
This rule applies to:
- Python scripts
- Configuration files
- Test files
- Any executable code
- Print statements
- Comments
- String literals

## Allowed
- Standard ASCII characters only (letters, numbers, basic punctuation)
- Standard ASCII symbols: `!@#$%^&*()_+-=[]{}|;:'",.<>?/~`

