## Rationale
Unicode characters can cause encoding errors in Windows environments, especially with cp1252 encoding. Using ASCII-only characters ensures code runs reliably across all platforms and environments.

## Enforcement
When writing or modifying code:
1. Replace Unicode checkmarks with `[PASS]` / `[FAIL]` / `[OK]` / `[ERROR]`
2. Replace emojis with descriptive text in brackets
3. Use ASCII-only symbols for visual indicators
4. Test that code runs without UnicodeEncodeError exceptions

